    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-03-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-03-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="313" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d313">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Lord Lyons</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-03-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 19, 1864</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Lord</hi>: I have the honor to recur to your two
                            notes of the 5th instant, one of which relates to the detention of three
                            of the crew of the British schooner Sallie, in jail at New York, and the
                            other to that of the master and crew of the British schooner Sylvanus,
                            at Fort Lafayette, and to inform your lordship that, at the
                            recommendation of this department, the Secretary of the Navy has
                            directed their discharge from custody.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, with high consideration, my lord, your obedient
                            servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Right Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Lord Lyons</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
